        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 5:59PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 10 miles west of Midway to
Ball to near Kolin. Movement was west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ball, Pollock, Dry Prong, Fishville, and Bentley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
